{"WERE":[{"def":"To guard; to protect.","pos":""}],"WEREGILD":[{"def":"The price of a man's head; a compensation paid of a man killed, partly to the king for the loss of a subject, partly to the lord of a vassal, and partly to the next of kin.","pos":""}],"WEREWOLF":[{"def":"A person transformed into a wolf in form and appetite, either temporarily or permanently, whether by supernatural influences, by witchcraft, or voluntarily; a lycanthrope.","pos":""}],"WERN":[{"def":"He is too great a niggard that will wern A man to light a candle at his lantern.","pos":""}],"WERNERIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to A.","pos":""}],"WERNERITE":[{"def":"The common grayish or white variety of soapolite.","pos":""}],"WEROOLE":[{"def":"An Australian lorikeet (Ptilosclera versicolor) noted for the variety of its colors; -- called also varied lorikeet.","pos":""}],"WERT":[{"def":", The second person singular, indicative and subjunctive moods, imperfect tense, of the verb be.","pos":""}]}